UTOR","type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"Look at this snippet: https://psalm.dev/r/6d99f50803\r\n\r\nhere function `usesCollection<T>(Collection<T> $col)` is allowed to add arbitrary value to the collection, even though it's type T is not known. To demonstrate the possibility of bugs, i've created a collection of strings, and via this function added an integer to it. Psalm noticed no errors.\r\n\r\nSuch behavior is disallowed in TypeScript:\r\n\r\n```ts\r\nclass Collection<T> {\r\n    constructor(private col: T[]) {}\r\n\r\n    add(element: T): void {\r\n        this.col.push(element);\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunction usesCollection<T>(col: Collection<T>) {\r\n    col.add(123);\r\n}\r\n```","closed_by":{"login":"muglug","id":2292638,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjIyOTI2Mzg=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/2292638?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/muglug","html_url":"https://github.com/muglug","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/muglug/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/muglug/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/muglug/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/muglug/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/muglug/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/muglug/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/muglug/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/muglug/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/muglug/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/vimeo/psalm/issues/2308/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://a